abstract: WNBA admits foul by Minnesota Lynx forward Maya Moore in league's Western Conference finals, which led to free throw and narrow victory by Phoenix Mercury, was called in error.
lead_paragraph: A foul that led to a winning free throw by Maya Moore of the Minnesota Lynx to eliminate the Phoenix Mercury should not have been called, the league said.

headline.main: W.N.B.A. Says Pivotal Call Was Wrong
